# Cursor Rule: UI/UX Mocks

**Applies to:** `apps/pwa/public/uiux/**`

Static HTML/CSS/JS mocks for designing screens before React implementation.

## Folder Structure

```
apps/pwa/public/uiux/
├── assets/                    # Shared images/icons for ALL screens
│   ├── bq-background-grid-map.png
│   ├── bq-ui-panel-frame-vertical.png
│   └── bq-ui-wide-button-states.png
├── 00-start-screen/           # Each screen in its own folder
│   ├── index.html             # HTML structure
│   ├── styles.css             # CSS styling
│   ├── script.js              # JavaScript behavior
│   └── README.md              # Screen documentation (optional)
└── {nn}-{screen-name}/        # Additional screens follow same pattern
```

## Rules

### File Organization
- **One folder per screen** — named `{nn}-{screen-name}/`
- **Three required files** — `index.html`, `styles.css`, `script.js`
- **Optional README.md** — documents the screen's purpose and implementation notes
- **Shared assets in `/assets/`** — images, icons, sprites used across screens

### Asset References
Use relative paths from screen folders to assets:
```css
/* styles.css */
background-image: url("../assets/bq-background-grid-map.png");
```

### Page Navigation (IMPORTANT)
**Always use explicit filenames** — CloudFront/S3 don't auto-resolve `index.html`:
```html
<!-- ✅ CORRECT - explicit filename -->
<a href="../01-tribute-setup/index.html">Next</a>

<!-- ❌ WRONG - may not work on CloudFront/S3 -->
<a href="../01-tribute-setup/">Next</a>
```

This ensures links work everywhere: local dev, S3, CloudFront, and direct file system access.

### Separation of Concerns
- **HTML** — Structure and semantic markup only
- **CSS** — All styling in `styles.css` (no inline styles)
- **JS** — All behavior in `script.js` (no inline scripts)

### No CSS/JS Inlining
Do NOT inline CSS or JS in HTML files. These are mocks but should follow clean separation:
```html
<!-- ✅ Correct -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
<script src="script.js"></script>

<!-- ❌ Wrong -->
<style>/* CSS here */</style>
<script>/* JS here */</script>
```

### README.md Format
Document each screen with:
1. **Purpose** — What the screen does
2. **Key Elements** — Table of UI components
3. **Implementation Notes** — For future React conversion
4. **Viewing** — How to preview the mock

### Adding New Screens
1. Create folder: `apps/pwa/public/uiux/{nn}-{screen-name}/`
2. Create files: `index.html`, `styles.css`, `script.js`
3. Optionally add `README.md`
4. Add any new shared images to `assets/`

## Viewing Mocks

```bash
pnpm dev:pwa
# Open: http://localhost:5173/uiux/{screen-name}/
```

Clean URLs work because each folder has an `index.html`.
